## Microsoft To-Do

Microsoft To-Do syncs via the Graph API. The easiest path is Azure CLI auth.

### 1. Install Azure CLI

```bash
brew install azure-cli   # macOS
```

### 2. Authenticate

```bash
az login
```

This opens a browser, you sign in with the same Microsoft account that holds your To-Do tasks.

### 3. First sync

```bash
uv run .claude/skills/tasks-import/import_tasks.py
```

⚠️ The template ships with a **stub implementation** for Microsoft To-Do. Full Graph API integration requires `azure-identity` + `msgraph-core`. See the SKILL.md and inline TODO in `import_tasks.py` for extension guidance, or reference the original Claude-Vault `todo-import` skill.

### Alternative: App Registration (non-interactive)

For launchd-scheduled syncs without interactive login:

1. https://portal.azure.com → **App registrations** → **New registration**
2. Add permission: Microsoft Graph → Delegated → `Tasks.Read`
3. Grant admin consent (or have your IT admin do so)
4. Copy the Application (client) ID and Directory (tenant) ID
5. Add to `.env`:
   ```
   AZURE_CLIENT_ID=...
   AZURE_TENANT_ID=...
   ```

{% elif task_provider == 'todoist' -%}
## Todoist

### 1. Get your API token

1. Go to https://todoist.com/app/settings/integrations/developer
2. Copy the **API token** (40-character hex string)

### 2. Add to .env

```bash
echo "TODOIST_API_TOKEN=your_token_here" >> .env
```

### 3. Sync

```bash
uv run .claude/skills/tasks-import/import_tasks.py
```

This pulls all active tasks and the last 200 completed tasks. Todoist rate-limits aren't hit at this scale — safe to run frequently.

### 4. Inspect

```bash
sqlite3 data/tasks.db
> SELECT title, status, due_date FROM tasks WHERE status='open' ORDER BY due_date;
```

{% elif task_provider == 'things' -%}
## Things 3

Things 3 stores its data in a local SQLite database. No auth needed — just Full Disk Access for macOS.

### 1. Grant Full Disk Access

System Settings → Privacy & Security → Full Disk Access → add Terminal.app (or your shell).

### 2. Sync

```bash
uv run .claude/skills/tasks-import/import_tasks.py
```

The script auto-discovers the Things database at:
```
~/Library/Group Containers/JLMPQHK86H.com.culturedcode.ThingsMac/ThingsData-*/Things Database.thingsdatabase/main.sqlite
```

### 3. Inspect

```bash
sqlite3 data/tasks.db
> SELECT title, status, completed_at FROM tasks WHERE provider='things' LIMIT 20;
```

### Notes

- Things 3 is macOS/iOS only
- The skill reads the Mac database; iOS/iPadOS tasks sync to the Mac via Things Cloud
- Read-only — this skill never modifies the Things database
